featured_reviews.review_id: A mosque is a place of worship for Muslims, who believe in one God called Allah. A mosque is also a center of community, where Muslims gather for prayer, education, social activities, and charity. A mosque can be any building or open space, as long as it has a niche called a mihrab that indicates the direction of Mecca, the holy city of Islam. A mosque may also have a tower called a minaret, from which a person called a muezzin calls the faithful to prayer five times a day. A mosque may also have a pulpit called a minbar, where a preacher delivers a sermon on Fridays. A mosque may also have a fountain or a pool for washing before prayer, and separate areas for men and women to pray. Mosques vary in size and style, depending on the region and the culture of the Muslims who built them. Some mosques are very simple and plain, while others are very ornate and decorated with tiles, domes, arches, and calligraphy. Some mosques are very old and historic, while others are very modern and innovative. Mosques are considered sacred places by Muslims, and they respect them by removing their shoes, covering their heads, and dressing modestly before entering them.

featured_reviews.review_id: A mosque is a place of worship for Muslims, who believe in one God called Allah. A mosque is also a center of community, where Muslims gather for prayer, education, social activities, and charity. A mosque can be any building or open space, as long as it has a niche called a mihrab that indicates the direction of Mecca, the holy city of Islam. A mosque may also have a tower called a minaret, from which a person called a muezzin calls the faithful to prayer five times a day. A mosque may also have a pulpit called a minbar, where a preacher delivers a sermon on Fridays. A mosque may also have a fountain or a pool for washing before prayer, and separate areas for men and women to pray. Mosques vary in size and style, depending on the region and the culture of the Muslims who built them. Some mosques are very simple and plain, while others are very ornate and decorated with tiles, domes, arches, and calligraphy. Some mosques are very old and historic, while others are very modern and innovative. Mosques are considered sacred places by Muslims, and they respect them by removing their shoes, covering their heads, and dressing modestly before entering them.

featured_reviews.review_id:
GoodIn the heart of Alukkal Mahallu, you'll discover a revered Juma Masjid, a place of congregational Friday prayers. This mosque holds a central position in the community, where locals gather for their spiritual nourishment and to strengthen their bonds of faith.

Adjacent to this sacred place, there is a college, creating a unique synergy of knowledge and spirituality. The college, attended by both students and teachers, shares a special connection with the mosque. It serves as a beacon of education, and the mosque, a sanctuary for spiritual reflection. Here, students and educators alike find solace and unity in their shared devotion, often coming together for prayers.

Alukkal Mahallu thrives as a community that embraces the values of education and faith. The Juma Masjid stands not only as a place of worship but also as a symbol of unity, where the local community, students, and teachers unite in their reverence for the divine and their pursuit of knowledge. It's a harmonious blend of spirituality and academia that enriches the lives of all who are a part of this vibrant community.

featured_reviews.review_translated_text: Padathe Palli Masjid is a very famous and oldest church located in Pattarkulam area. History teaches us that Mamburum came to this area and gave instructions to build a mosque. In the past, Nalakali cultivation was a profession that many people depended on. During the time of the Mahanavars, when the four-legged animals got sick and became dead, the Mahanavars were approached and thus the famous leg washing is done here today on the instructions of the Mahanavars.
